headline: Heard on the Street Monday Recap: Risk On Again
summary: Stocks rallied after the Senate advanced a measure designed to end the government shutdown.  Magnificent Seven companies and other technology stocks led the way.  The Nasdaq composite gained 2.3%, while the S&P 500 rose 1.5% and the Dow industrials climbed 0.8%.
